<section class="manual-section mb-4">
  <h2 class="h5">Quick Start</h2>
  <ol class="manual-list">
    <li><strong>Create a function:</strong> Go to Functions > New. Add name, date, and status.</li>
    <li><strong>Notes:</strong> Capture key info, requirements, and internal updates.</li>
    <li><strong>Menus:</strong> Add menu(s) and adjust quantities/prices if needed.</li>
    <li><strong>Quote:</strong> Confirm totals, add discount or payments, and review remaining balance.</li>
    <li><strong>Proposal:</strong> Open builder, choose what the client sees, then send the client link.</li>
  </ol>
</section>

<section class="manual-section mb-4">
  <h2 class="h5">Full Guide</h2>
  <h3 class="h6">1) Function Info</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Set event name, date, time, room, and group size in the Details sidebar.</li>
    <li>Use status to track progress: lead, qualified, confirmed, balance due, completed.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="h6">2) Contacts</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Add contacts, set a primary contact, and keep phone/email up to date.</li>
    <li>Use the contact menu to edit or remove a linked contact.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="h6">3) Notes</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Log key details, client requests, and internal instructions.</li>
    <li>Mark note types appropriately (proposal, internal, call) for clarity.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="h6">4) Tasks</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Create tasks for follow ups, deposits, or room setup checks.</li>
    <li>Assign due dates and close tasks as they are completed.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="h6">5) Menus</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Add menus by category, then review menu items and quantities.</li>
    <li>Use include toggles to hide items from proposals if needed.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="h6">6) Quote</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Adjust quantities and prices. Subtotals update automatically.</li>
    <li>Add a discount if approved. It appears as a line item in totals.</li>
    <li>Add payments with description, method, and date paid.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="h6">7) Proposal Builder</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Choose the menus, notes, and terms shown to the client.</li>
    <li>Preview the proposal and send the client link by email.</li>
    <li>Apply client selections back into the quote if required.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="h6">8) Communications</h3>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Review inbound emails and log important communications.</li>
    <li>Use the client link to update selections when required.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="manual-section mb-4">
  <h2 class="h5">Reports</h2>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Use Reports to review revenue, costs, and profit over time.</li>
    <li>Filter by date ranges or status to match monthly summaries.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="manual-section mb-4">
  <h2 class="h5">Setup Checklist</h2>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>Set Rooms / Spaces and capacities.</li>
    <li>Create Menu Categories, Menus, Choices, and Units.</li>
    <li>Confirm Proposal Terms and default templates.</li>
    <li>Review Event Types and Calendar settings.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="manual-section mb-2">
  <h2 class="h5">Common Issues</h2>
  <ul class="manual-list">
    <li>If totals look off, refresh the quote and confirm item quantities.</li>
    <li>If a menu is missing in a proposal, resync from the menu options.</li>
    <li>For payment discrepancies, verify the payment list and discount lines.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
